"Abstract Walsall M.B.C., in conjunction with ICL, are developing an expert system to give advice on welfare benefits. The system will advise potential claimants on their entitlement, initially to Income Support, Family Credit, Mobility Allowance, Attendance Allowance and Invalid Care Allowance with other benefits to be added later on. Although the present version covers only 5 of the approximately 70 benefits, in fact these 5 benefits account for about 85% of claims to the DSS. The system is currently on field trial in six of the Council's Neighbourhood Offices. The following summarises developments so far."
